---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import CTA from "../../components/CTA.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="When Should You Hire a Fractional CTO?"
  description="Learn when startups benefit most from fractional CTO leadership."
>
  <Header />

  <main>
    <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem; color:var(--color-navy); margin-top:3rem;">
      When Should You Hire a Fractional CTO?
    </h1>

    <p style="max-width:700px; margin-top:1rem; color:#475569;">
      A fractional CTO provides strategic technology leadership without the cost of a full-time executive.
      But when is the right time to bring one on?
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:2rem; color:var(--color-navy);">1. You’re building your first product</h2>
    <p style="max-width:700px; color:#475569;">
      Founders often need help choosing the right architecture, stack, and roadmap.
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:2rem; color:var(--color-navy);">2. Engineering velocity is slowing down</h2>
    <p style="max-width:700px; color:#475569;">
      A fractional CTO can diagnose bottlenecks and improve execution.
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:2rem; color:var(--color-navy);">3. You’re preparing for fundraising</h2>
    <p style="max-width:700px; color:#475569;">
      Investors want clarity on technology, risks, and scalability.
    </p>

    <CTA />
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
